- GUI:
> python hsim2.py

- Command line:
> python hsim2.py -c -p 4 test_point2.fits 200 50 K 10x10 0.71 1.1 2 280 True 100 0.

- Help:
> python hsim2.py -h
-------------------
 HARMONI Simulator
-------------------
Version:  200
---
TO RUN GUI
>>> python hsim2.py

Command line
>>> python hsim2.py -c arg arg2 ...

---
OPTIONS
-h or --help = display this message and exit
-c or --cline = use command line. Use: >>> python hsim2.py -c to display arguments list
-p or --proc = set the number of processors when using command line (1-8)
-o or --odir = set the output file directory when using the command line (default: ./output_cubes)


> python hsim2.py -c
COMMAND LINE USAGE

Enter command line arguments in following order:
1. datacube: Input datacube filepath
2. DIT: Detector Integration Time [s]
3. NDIT: No. of exposures
4. grating: [V+R, Iz+J, H+K, Iz, J, H, K, z, J-high, H-high, K-high]
5. spax: spatial pixel (spaxel) scale [mas] - 4x4, 10x10, 20x20, 30x60 
6. seeing: Atmospheric seeing FWHM [arcsec] - 0.63", 0.71", 0.84", 1.11", 1.32"
7. air mass - 1.1, 1.3, 1.5, 2.0
8. jitter: Additional telescope PSF blur [mas]
9. site temp: Site/telescope temperature [K]
10. ADR on/off: (True/False) - atmospheric differential refraction
11. noise seed
12. background variation [%]


